-- China to Expand Surveillance Ship Fleet to Protect Interests, Daily Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-27T23:17:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/china-to-expand-surveillance-ship-fleet-to-protect-interests-daily-says.html
China will increase the number of
ships in the surveillance fleet under the State Oceanic
Administration to better protect its maritime rights, the China
Daily reported today, citing an unidentified official at the
government agency.  A 77-meter-long inspection ship was added to the fleet
yesterday, according to the report. China will also add an
additional 36 ships, the Beijing-based newspaper reported.  Of the new ships to be added to the fleet, seven will be in
the 1,500 tons category, with 15 others in the 1,000 tons
category and the rest in the 600 tons category, according to the
report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  